## Keyboard Shortcuts

Required on every new section — index, show, new, edit, bulk bar, and modals.

Root element: `data-controller="keyboard-shortcuts"`

Annotate links/buttons with:
```erb
data: { keyboard_shortcuts_target: "trigger", keyboard_shortcuts_key: "e" }
```

Show hint: `<kbd class="rounded border border-gray-200 bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs font-normal text-gray-400">e</kbd>`

Standard shortcuts (adapt labels in help overlay; keep keys consistent across sections):
- Index: `n` new, `p`/`t`/`a`/`d` bulk actions, `j`/`k` navigate, `x` toggle select, `↵` view focused, `?` help
- Show: `e` edit, resource-specific keys for modal actions, `a` archive/unarchive, `d` delete, `u` back, `?` help
- Modals: `↵` submit, `Esc` cancel/close
- Forms: `Enter` submit (after exiting field with Esc)

Help overlay: `data-keyboard-shortcuts-target="help"`, sections grouped by context (list, navigation, item view, modals). Copy the overlay structure from `inboxes/index.html.erb` and customize the action names.
